(secondQuint)Stonewall Treatment Evaluation Project.

 Stonewall Project clients who have initiated treatment within the past 60 days will be eligible for the outcome evaluation.

 20% of clients are likely to be on parole or probation; these clients will be eligible to participate in the study.

 Outcome measures that will be examined as part of the treatment outcome evaluation include: 1) self-reported substance use; 2) urine toxicology screening; and 3) sex risk taking.

